# EP 9 — HTTP vs HTTPS

## What is HTTP?
HTTP stands for HyperText Transfer Protocol.
The language browsers use to talk to websites.
- All data sent in plain text
- Anyone can read it
- No encryption at all
- Very dangerous for sensitive data!

## What is HTTPS?
HTTPS stands for HTTP Secure.
Same as HTTP but with full encryption!
- All data is encrypted
- Nobody can read it in transit
- Shows a lock icon in browser
- S stands for Secure — SSL/TLS encryption

## HTTP vs HTTPS Comparison
HTTP ❌
- No encryption
- Data visible to anyone
- No lock icon
- Dangerous for passwords and cards

HTTPS ✅
- Fully encrypted
- Data protected in transit
- Lock icon shown in browser
- Safe for sensitive data

## Key Rule
Always check for the lock icon
before entering any password or
sensitive information on a website!

